## Request State

<%= partial "includes/codesnippets/requeststate.md.erb" %>

Request the state of devices. Leave `device_state_list` empty to request the state of all devices.

### HTTP Request

`POST area/requeststate`

### Request Body

Param | Type | O/M | Description
------|------|-----|------------
device_list | array[object] | Mandatory | A list comprised of one or more devices.
device_ID | string | Mandatory | The network ID used to identify the device on the network.
transaction_ID | string | Optional | The transaction initiated through an API call from your application.
session_token | string | Mandatory | One-time token used to establish a session for a user and is revoked when the token expires. It contains the location at which the session token will be used.

<aside class="success">
A successful request returns a status of 200 OK with device state(s).
</aside>

### Response

Param | Type | O/M | Description
------|------|-----|------------
device_state_list | array[object] | Mandatory | A list of devices and their statuses. Possible values are Online, Offline, or DeviceError.
device_ID | string | Mandatory | The network ID used to identify the device on the network.
transaction_ID | string | Optional | The transaction initiated through an API call from your application.

<aside class="warning">
An unsuccessful request may return a 400 error code with an explanatory message. For the general meaning of these responses, see the Error Codes section of this document.
</aside>